2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 52
BY SENATOR EDMONDS
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Intercessors for America for their Spiritual Heritage Project and to
acknowledge Almighty God as the Author of liberty on the two hundred fiftieth
anniversary of the founding of these United States of America.
WHEREAS, we acknowledge Almighty God as Sovereign over the nations and the
Author of Liberty, and we bow before Him in thanks as a state on this two hundred fiftieth
anniversary of the founding of these United States of America; and
WHEREAS, with hearts full of gratitude, we thank Almighty God for the blessings
that He has bestowed upon the state of Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, with reverence, we acknowledge Almighty God and His providence that
has guided us through trials and triumphs as a state and a nation; and
WHEREAS, with humility, we confess the times that we have strayed from His
ways; and
WHEREAS, two and a half centuries ago, our founders, in the heat of the American
Revolution and the hope of a transformation, declared, "All men are created equal and
endowed by their Creator with unalienable rights, that among these are life, liberty and the
pursuit of happiness…"; and
WHEREAS, our founders looked to Almighty God as the source of true liberty and,
in doing so, laid the cornerstone of a nation that would become a beacon of freedom to the
world; and
WHEREAS, Almighty God has poured out blessings upon our state and nation with
abundant natural resources, vast and varied landscapes, and a people endowed with ingenuity
and resilience; and
WHEREAS, the Constitution the founders framed is undergirded by moral conviction
and spiritual awareness and unleashed the greatest experiment in self-government the world
